{"aid": "40174295", "title": "Rat Tickling Certificate Course", "url": "https://www.nc3rs.org.uk/3rs-resources/rat-tickling/rat-tickling-certification", "domain": "nc3rs.org.uk", "votes": 2, "user": "aragonite", "posted_at": "2024-04-26 21:07:11", "comments": 0, "source_title": "Rat tickling: Certification | NC3Rs", "source_text": "Rat tickling: Certification | NC3Rs\n\nSkip to main content\n\nInternational 3Rs Prize now open for applications. \u00a330k prize (\u00a32k personal\naward) for outstanding science with demonstrable 3Rs impacts.\n\n  * 3Rs for the public\n  * News\n  * Events\n  * Sign in\n\nE-learning\n\n# Rat tickling: Certification\n\nThis online course from Purdue University, which was funded by the Animal\nWelfare Institute, was created by Dr Megan LaFollette (North American 3Rs\nCollaborative) and colleagues with the aim of allowing you to become certified\nin the correct rat tickling technique.\n\nThis course is best for individuals who want to apply rat tickling in their\nfacilities and receive a certificate for their efforts.\n\nAt the end of this course, you will be able to:\n\n  * Describe the purpose and benefits of rat tickling\n  * Practically implement rat tickling in your facility\n  * Recognise signs that rats are responding positively or negatively to tickling\n\nThe course is divided into six main sections; you need to pass a quiz at the\nend of each section before proceeding to the next.\n\nThe course is estimated to take between 30 minutes to 2 hours to complete.\nHowever, you can access the course at any time and complete it in multiple\nsessions.\n\nAccess the rat tickling certification course now via google API.\n\nFor those who do not wish do get a certificate there is the option of\nundertaking the rat tickling open course, which will allow you to learn a few\nthings about rat tickling. You can access the rat tickling open course using\nthe link above, in the highlighted box - just click on the 'open course'\noption when prompted.\n\n## Rat tickling resources\n\n### Overview\n\n### Flyer\n\n### Webinar\n\nFirst published\n\n30 March 2020\n\nLast updated\n\n19 August 2021\n\n  * Twitter\n  * Facebook\n  * Email\n\n## More from the NC3Rs\n\n### Useful links\n\n  * Contact us\n  * What we do\n  * Our team\n  * NC3Rs careers\n\n### The 3Rs\n\n  * 3Rs definitions\n  * 3Rs for the public\n\n### Legal and privacy\n\n  * Accessibility\n  * Privacy and cookie policy\n  * Terms and conditions\n\n### Other sites from the NC3Rs\n\n  * ARRIVE guidelines\n  * CRACK IT Innovation Platform\n  * Experimental Design Assistant\n  * The NC3Rs gateway\n\n  * Twitter\n  * Facebook\n  * LinkedIn\n  * YouTube\n\n  * \u00a9 NC3Rs\n  * Contact us\n\n", "frontpage": false}
